@js-eval text
Use js-eval for bounded procedural logic, data reshaping, exact arithmetic, local search, and controlled variant updates that benefit from explicit JavaScript.
Prefer it when the step needs loops, collections, graph traversal, shortest-path search, object manipulation, or direct state edits through ~family handles.
It is especially appropriate for exact algorithmic sub-problems where the runtime should expose inspectable computation instead of asking an LLM to improvise steps or numeric results.
Do not use it for plain prose generation, free-form reasoning, or tasks that can be expressed as short when/then rules or deterministic templates.
Bodies should be real JavaScript that reads $family values and uses ~family or sop helpers for writes and structural effects.
